{"id": "EUVD-2024-51820", "enisaUuid": "72362b60-026f-3f8d-86a0-aa35444bc967", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\ncomedi: Flush partial mappings in error case\n\nIf some remap_pfn_range() calls succeeded before one failed, we still have\nbuffer pages mapped into the userspace page tables when we drop the buffer\nreference with comedi_buf_map_put(bm). The userspace mappings are only\ncleaned up later in the mmap error path.\n\nFix it by explicitly flushing all mappings in our VMA on the error path.\n\nSee commit 79a61cc3fc04 (\"mm: avoid leaving partial pfn mappings around in\nerror case\").", "datePublished": "2024-12-24T12:30:42", "dateUpdated": "2025-11-03T21:31:45", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/57f048c2d205b85e34282a9b0b0ae177e84c2f44", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/b9322408d83accc8b96322bc7356593206288c56", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/8797b7712de704dc231f9e821d8eb3b9aeb3a032", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/16c507df509113c037cdc0ba642b9ab3389bd26c", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/9b07fb464eb69a752406e78e62ab3a60bfa7b00d", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/c6963a06ce5c61d3238751ada04ee1569663a828", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/297f14fbb81895f4ccdb0ad25d196786d6461e00", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/ce8f9fb651fac95dd41f69afe54d935420b945bd", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2024-53148", "https://lists.debian.org/debian-lts-announce/2025/03/msg00001.html", "https://lists.debian.org/debian-lts-announce/2025/03/msg00002.html"], "aliases": ["CVE-2024-53148"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.04, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "1668574f-3d9f-3207-965f-c6c3c8daa549", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "ed9eccbe8970f6eedc1b978c157caf1251a896d4 <57f048c2d205b85e34282a9b0b0ae177e84c2f44"}, {"id": "2890456c-7ddc-361f-8c21-22933ba42d07", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "ed9eccbe8970f6eedc1b978c157caf1251a896d4 <16c507df509113c037cdc0ba642b9a